channel.name: funhouse-challenge
channel.topic:
Build a funhouse that's full of fun interactive surprises and sounds around every corner. Have some creative fun with this April fools inspired challenge!
Challenge dates: March 30 – April 13

messages.content:
It’s a Funhouse Challenge! 🤪 🏠 

Trapdoors! Fun surprises! What's best for April fools? Can you build a funhouse that's full of fun interactive surprises and sounds around every corner? We think you're up for this fun April fools inspired challenge!

:timer: Challenge dates: March 30 – April 13

__Guidelines__
:earth: Your creation must be built entirely by you and in Minecraft Earth.
:crafting_table: Your build must be a brand new creation, crafted just for this challenge.
:buildplate: Build big or small! Build plate size won’t be a factor in judging.
:sign: Post your image or video submission in #funhouse-challenge by the deadline. Feel free to ask a Moderator to pin it!
:challenges: Winning submissions may be used in social media posts.
:fast_parrot: Have fun!

There's no cinematic masterpiece with a cast of thousands this round - the gang are all dutifully observing social isolation (with the exception of Jay, who is busy training to become the worlds first Vogue cover model to become a professional zombie hunter)

Instead, I leave you in the capable hands of our tour guide, an only *slightly* murderous mime who promises not to kill you *too* much.

I can't, however, vouch for his friends.......

The overall style of this build is a little bit steampunk, a little bit carnivale, a little bit brain-teasing, and a little bit NOPE-NOPE-nope-nope-nope-ⁿᵒᵖᵉⁿᵒᵖᵉⁿᵒᵖᵉⁿᵒᵖᵉᵃᵃᴬᴬᴬᴴᴴᴴᴳᴴⁿᵍʰⁿ

They made the video drag on a bit so they got cut, but a demonstration will probably turn up in #builds before too long.

Music is by Robert Austin - the aptly named *'Circus of Dread'* available on Bandcamp.
